From 483cc80035a2a31f2ad5acaa99ba72edbc95d316 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 16 Jul 2026 13:58:25 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix shorthand-vs-longhand cascade origin precedence

A higher-precedence author shorthand (e.g. `background: lime`) failed to
override a lower-precedence user-agent longhand (e.g. `background-color:
white`): the post-cascade shorthand expansion is `!ContainsKey`-gated, so it
keeps any already-present longhand regardless of origin. Only margin/padding
seeded their longhands into the cascade, so the leak hit background (and the
border families).

Generalize the longhand seeding (AddShorthandLonghandSlots) to reuse the
canonical ExpandCssShorthands expander for every modelled shorthand, so each
shorthand competes for its longhands by origin/specificity/source order. The
border/border-<side> shorthands are excluded because their omitted-component
reset to initial is handled by the separate origin-blind
ApplyBorderShorthandResets pass, which requires those longhands to be absent.

Unblocks native <dialog> UA box-chrome (an author `dialog { background:
transparent }` reset must beat the UA `background-color: white` longhand;
WPT anchor-position-top-layer-003/004/006).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
